title: Slash Feat. Myles Kennedy - April 26, 2015 - Rockville - FL
description:
Enjoy, from your friend JITF! =)

* Please feel free to convert/chop/edit/share however you like. I only ask that you keep the Taper's notes and other files with it for posterity and context.


Slash featuring Myles Kennedy & The Conspirators
5:40 PM
Sunday, April 26, 2015
Rockville Festival - Jack Daniel's Stage
Jacksonville, Florida, USA


Band Lineup:

Slash (Lead Guitar)
Frank Sidoris (Rhythm Guitar)
Todd Kerns (Bass Guitar, Backup Vocals)
Brent Fitz (Drums)
Myles Kennedy (Lead Vocals)



RECORDING INFO:

Device: Sony PCM-M10
Microphone: Sony ECM-DS70P Electret Condenser Stereo Microphone
Recorded Quality: Lossless PCM
Sampling Rate: 48 kHz
Bit Depth: 24-bit
Editing: .WAV file split with Sony Sound Forge Audio Studio 9.0d LE
Conversion: EZ CD Audio Converter v3.0.6 [64-Bit]
Checksums: .MD5 & .ST5 files created with Trader's Little Helper v 2.7.0 (build 172)
Lineage: Sony PCM-M10 > .WAV > .FLAC (Level 8)


Bootleged by:
JITF (JumpInTheFire)


Setlist:

01. Intro
02. You're A Lie
03. Nightrain (Guns N' Roses Cover)
04. Back From Cali
05. You Could Be Mine (Guns N' Roses Cover)
06. Meant To Fly
07. World On Fire
08. Anastasia
09. Sweet Child O' Mine (Guns N' Roses Cover)
10. Band Introduction
11. Slither (Velvet Revolver Cover)
12. Paradise City (Guns N' Roses Cover)

Runtime: 58 minutes, 18 seconds


Recording Comments:

Great concert, the recording came out nicely, the only issue would be that it's not extremely loud due to my positioning in the crowd. I was back about half-way standing next to the soundboard/cameras area.


Recording 'Proof' Comments:

On track 03, "Nightrain" at 5:02-5:03, Myles Kennedy says, "Good afternoon Jacksonville". The rest of the recording has other mentions as well
